  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assistance d&#x2019;urgence aux populations du Cameroun affect&#xE9;es par le conflit : Matrice de Suivi des D&#xE9;placements &#x2013; &#xC9;valuation cibl&#xE9;e des Besoins et Tendance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to ensure an adequate response to the needs of the populations affected by the conflicts in the Far North region of Cameroon (Logone et Chari, Mayo Sava and Mayo Tsanaga). IOM will perform targeted needs assessments and monitor displacements using the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM), among other activities. 342,416 refugees and displaced people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within 9 months.</narrative>
  </description>
